# VenusOS-Tailscale

Installs [Tailscale](https://tailscale.com) VPN on Venus OS, enabling SSH access from anywhere — even behind 4G CGNAT (Bouygues, SFR, etc.).

## Requirements

- Venus OS v3.50 or later
- SetupHelper (PackageManager) installed
- Internet access on the RPi at install time (to download Tailscale binary)
- A free Tailscale account: https://tailscale.com

## Installation via PackageManager

1. In Venus OS PackageManager, add package: `florent1080/VenusOS-Tailscale`
2. Install the package
3. Edit `/data/tailscale/tailscale.conf`:
   - Go to https://login.tailscale.com/admin/settings/keys
   - Create a key: **Reusable** + **No expiry**
   - Paste the key as `AUTHKEY=tskey-auth-...`
   - Set `HOSTNAME=venus-van` (or any name you want)
4. Run: `/data/VenusOS-Tailscale/tailscale_connect.sh`
   - Or simply reboot — the service will authenticate automatically

## After install

- SSH from anywhere: `ssh root@venus-van` (or use the `100.x.x.x` Tailscale IP)
- Check status: `tailscale status`
- View in Tailscale admin: https://login.tailscale.com/admin/machines

## Files

- `/data/tailscale/tailscale.conf` — configuration (AUTHKEY, HOSTNAME)
- `/data/tailscale/bin/` — tailscale + tailscaled binaries (auto-downloaded)
- `/data/tailscale/state/` — Tailscale state (auth token, etc.)
- `/service/tailscaled/` — runit service (auto-started at boot)

## Notes

- The Tailscale binary is downloaded at install time from pkgs.tailscale.com
- Supports RPi3 (ARMv7) and RPi5 (ARM64) — detected automatically
- Config is preserved on uninstall/upgrade
- Works behind CGNAT (no port forwarding needed)
